BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sing a Better Future Into Existence
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T150000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000
UID:260227w_g_6W5Y2E2quDZqzlfy1g
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/GNvy5oxRZkODTjkRyc7o5Q.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us on March 14 from 3 to 5 p.m. at Trinity Lutheran Churc
 h\, 3637 Golf Road\, Evanston\, for an afternoon of public community singi
 ng — learning and singing songs together as a practice of courage\, soli
 darity\, and hope. Singing in community steadies our breath\, strengthens 
 our bonds\, and helps us remember that we belong to one another. It also p
 repares us for faithful\, public\, nonviolent witness. \n\nThis gathering
  is non-partisan and deeply political\, in that it expresses our vision 
 for a world of peace and justice for all our neighbors\, near and far. \
 n\nHosted by Trinity Lutheran Church\, this event is open to people of eve
 ry religious tradition and those with no religious commitments at all who 
 share that vision. No musical background is needed. If you can breathe\, y
 ou can sing! \n\nA donation will be invited. All proceeds benefit mutual 
 aid networks in Minneapolis-St. Paul. You can register online here: https
 ://app.tickettailor.com/events/commonpulse/2081933
LOCATION:Trinity Lutheran Church
URL:https://www.trinityevanston.org/events/sing-a-better-future-into-exist
 ence
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jackalope Theatre Company's "The Dress-Up Play
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T140000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T150000
UID:260227RsXauXsuVU29ZU9AewrsLg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/GSS7Hs-y8UudGJV9-Z5G0Q.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Jackalope Theatre Company is proud to present its first produc
 tion for young audiences and the launch of its 18th season with the world 
 premiere of The Dress-Up Play by Juliet Kang Huneke\, March 7 - 22\, direc
 ted by Karina Patel\, at the Broadway Armory Park\, 5917 N Broadway St. Th
 e running time is 60 minutes with no intermission. \n\nThe Dress-Up Play 
 is a new family-friendly production from Jackalope. New friends gather in 
 a bedroom to play dress up. But who gets to wear what? Do our clothes have
  to match what we look like outside? And what if our outside doesn’t mat
 ch our inside? Filled with tutus\, fake mustaches\, scarves and fierce run
 way walks. The Dress-Up Play is an immersive fashion party for all ages th
 at celebrates self-expression\, open-mindedness and the wholeness of every
 one.\n\nThe performance schedule is Fridays at 7 p.m. and Saturdays and Su
 ndays at 2 p.m. Tickets are $15 - $35 with student and Edgewater resident 
 discounts available. Subscription and single tickets are now available at 
 JackalopeTheatre.org or call/text the box office at 773.340.2543.
LOCATION:Broadway Armory Park
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/jackalope-theatre-company-s-the-dress-up-play/18232212/2026-03-
 14T14
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
