BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Reading the Cards: A Tarot Study Group
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T180000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T193000
UID:260309zCM-G5k-FEOCQAKbfmAX3A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/PEgP9xeE1ESFUr4NxaAmqQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Picking up a tarot deck for the first time can feel overwhelmi
 ng. Seventy-eight cards\, all that symbolism\, and no idea where to begin.
  The good news? You don't need to memorize anything to start reading. You 
 just need a little guidance and a willingness to look closely at what's in
  front of you.\n\nIn this hands-on workshop\, participants will use Stefa
 nie Caponi's Guided Tarot as a roadmap to start reading cards with confide
 nce. Rather than memorizing textbook definitions\, we'll explore exercises
  from the book that help you develop your own relationship with the cards 
 using intuition\, observation\, and storytelling.\n\nThe box set includes 
 a Rider Waite Smith deck\, which is the foundation most modern tarot decks
  are built on. Learning with this deck gives you a visual language that tr
 ansfers to nearly any other deck you pick up down the road\, making it an 
 especially smart starting point for anyone planning to continue learning o
 r take future workshops.\n\nYou'll leave with practical skills you can use
  immediately: how to do a simple reading for yourself\, how to interpret w
 hat you see \\(not just what you've been told a card means\\)\, and a fram
 ework for continued practice at home.\n\nNo experience necessary. You don'
 t need to "believe" in anything\, just bring your curiosity.
LOCATION:Bookends & Beginnings
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/reading-the-cards-a-tarot-study-group/18280895/2026-03-18T18
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
