BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:20-Hour Foundations of Equity Training
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T100000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T150000
UID:260227Qv8A72Fn30Cna566jjgocQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/FFeeokvKs0ebTYTFBU_a-g.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore is offering a powerful\, 20-hour fo
 undational equity training designed specifically for leaders who shape wor
 kplaces\, institutions\, and communities.\n\nThis is a structured\, in-dep
 th learning experience that equips leaders with historical understanding\,
  practical tools\, and relational skills needed to lead more equitably and
  effectively in today’s complex environments. There is special pricing 
 available for Nonprofit professionals and Educators.\n\nWhy Equity Trainin
 g?\n\nCommunities and organizations are facing major change\, heightened e
 xpectations around equity\, and increasingly diverse teams. Leaders are be
 ing called to respond with clarity\, confidence\, and competence.\n\nThis 
 training helps participants:\n\nUnderstand the historical roots of systemi
 c inequities and how they continue to shape present-day systems\n\nIdentif
 y how policies\, practices\, and cultural norms can reinforce inequity or 
 strengthen equity\n\nStrengthen an ability to lead across differences and 
 change\n\nDevelop practical strategies for creating inclusive\, accountabl
 e spaces\n\nWho This Is For:\n\nWhether you lead a nonprofit\, manage a de
 partment\, chair a board\, or convene a professional network\, this traini
 ng provides foundational knowledge and applied tools that translate direct
 ly into your leadership practice.\n\nThis program represents a significant
  value for organizations seeking meaningful professional development witho
 ut the cost of private consulting engagements!\n\nNOTE: This training can 
 be used toward ICDVP CEUs for professionals working in domestic violence p
 revention.\n\nSeats are limited.\n\nIf your organization is committed to l
 eading with integrity\, strengthening culture\, and serving your community
  more equitably\, this is the right opportunity for you.\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\
 _\n\nDATE/TIME: March 16th\, 2026 - March 20th\, 2026 \\(M-F\\) from 10am
  -3pm CST\n\nPRICE: $200 for standard ticketing per person\, $150 for Nonp
 rofit Professionals and Educators\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\nQUESTIONS…? CONT
 ACT:\n\nRoger Moreano\, Senior Director of Institutional and Community Equ
 ity\n\nrmoreano@ywca-ens.org\n\n847-864-8445 ext. 1128
LOCATION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/20-hour-foundations-of-equity-training-ti
 ckets-1983364569819?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=attendeeshare&utm-medi
 um=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebdsshcopyurl
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
