DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T160000
UID:2602122djW06car06TdcPTPfV2nA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/CT7F4yijQ0aXrT9eldBcGg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Women artists have historically remained in relative obscurity
  due to several factors including societal pressures prioritizing domestic
 ity and systemic exclusion. This exhibit showcases women artists from our 
 collection of 20th century art and seeks to open the door to many more und
 errepresented Evanston women artists. Exhibit opens February 14 and runs t
 hrough April 12\, 2026.
LOCATION:Evanston History Center
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/unveiling-evanston-women-artists/17988797/2026-03-20T13
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Birth of the Cool: Mulligan Mosaics Nonet
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T193000
UID:260203akJIuO-vsUWsAwp-VC7kwA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Q2t66VdqB0mdtakLB1q28w.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join the Mulligan Mosaics Nonet as they celebrate the centenni
 al of Miles Davis’ birth with a complete performance of his landmark alb
 um\, “The Birth of the Cool.” Culled from a multitude of source materi
 al\, the nonet will be performing the actual arrangements as orchestrated 
 by the likes of Gil Evans\, John Lewis\, Gerry Mulligan\, and others.\n\nC
 had McCullough\, trumpet\; Dan Nicholson\, alto sax\; Ryan Schulz\, bass t
 rumpet\; Momo Hasselbring Seko\, French horn\; Ted Hogarth\, baritone sax\
 ; John Blane\, tuba\; Kevin Fort\, piano\; Joe Policastro\, bass\; Todd Ho
 well\, drums.\n\nThis concert is generously sponsored by the Music Perfor
 mance Trust Fund \\(MPTF\\).\n\nThe event is free and open to the public.\
 n\nFor any further questions about the event\, reach out to either smat@n
 orthpark.edu or 773-244-5630.
LOCATION:Anderson Chapel | North Park University
URL:https://www.northpark.edu/event-calendar/the-birth-of-the-cool-mulliga
 n-mosaics-nonet/
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
