 ical  education wing\, libraries\, and fine arts/performing arts areas.\n\
 n \n\nProsp ective or new ETHS families\, District 202 community members\,
  business owne rs\, and people who work in Evanston/Skokie organizations o
 r businesses are  invited to attend. Please allow a total of 1.5 hours for
  this event. The  tour will last approximately 60 minutes\, followed by an
  optional 20-minute  Q&A session. Tours are hosted by ETHS staff with supp
 ort from ETHS Ambass adors.\n\n \n\nWhile childcare is not provided\, chil
 dren may attend ETHS Campu s Tour days with a registered adult\; please no
 te that tours are not recomm ended for children under the age of 5 or peop
 le with limited mobility due  to extensive walking.\n\n \n\nRegistration f
 or Campus Tours opens approximatel y one month before each tour date. If y
 our preferred tour date is not avai lable at this time\, please visit the 
 registration page again soon. \n\n \n\nFo r more information\, contact the
