BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Make America Great Again -  A Short History of American Fascism
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T140000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T160000
UID:260312s6Bj_yWHpEChSgeqPYww1g
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/mad7iZ1NUU6KE3IXUL66gw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:One Year of Trump 2.0 How did we get here?!\n\nMake America Gr
 eat Again - A Short History of American Fascism from the Ku Klux Klan to t
 he Age of Trump\n\nJohn Donoghue\, an associate professor of history at Lo
 yola University Chicago is leading this forum based on a lecture he gave a
 t Loyola University late last year and his new book project American Insur
 rections: An Unruly History of White Nationalism\, which traces how insurr
 ectionary violence established white supremacy in the colonial era and pla
 yed a vital part in its transition to white nationalism in the United Stat
 es and the resurgence of white Christian supremacy after the Civil War. As
  the book concludes\, paramilitary violence became the strategic acceleran
 t in white Christian nationalism's passage into American fascism in the tw
 entieth and twenty-first centuries.His earlier work has focused on the his
 tory of early American colonialism\, radical political thought and action\
 , slavery and servitude\, abolition\, and the political economy of capital
 ism. His earlier work focused on the history of early American colonialism
 \, radical political thought and action\, slavery and servitude\, abolitio
 n\, and the political economy of capitalism. The event is sponsored by Re
 fuse Fascism Chicago and is endorsed by Northside Friends Meeting Ministry
  on Racism Committee and Evanston Neighbors for Peace.
LOCATION:Evanston Main Library
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/make-america-great-again-a-short-history-of-american-fascism/18
 314138/2026-03-22T14
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
