BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Concert featuring pianist Sarah Loisch
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T120000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T123000
UID:2603124aiaCRLZyUWPeekAFfFbsg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Etfqidy3LEyCNAPyQ4UGnQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Monday\, March 23\, 2026\, at 12pm \\(Noon\\) for a
  concert featuring pianist Sarah Loisch. This is Sarah’s second appearan
 ce in our concert series\, and we know it will be a treat! The concert is 
 free and open to the public\, and an offering will be collected with 50% g
 oing to the performer and the other half supporting St. Mark’s Piano and
  Organ Fund. For more information\, please contact Westley at music@stmark
 sevanston.org. \n\nDetails: St. Mark’s Episcopal Church \\(1509 Ridge A
 ve\, Evanston\\). Parking is limited to street parking\, but plenty is wit
 hin walking distance. \n\nMeet the performer:\n\nSarah Loisch began her m
 usical studies at an early age alongside her six older siblings in Kokomo\
 , Indiana where the family’s active involvement in vocal and instrumenta
 l learning led to performances across the state. Upon discovering a deep c
 onnection to piano literature\, she committed to full-time musical studies
  and has since been an active collaborator and performer with orchestras a
 nd ensembles\, including the Indiana Wind Symphony and the Heartland Festi
 val Orchestra. As a performer\, Miss Loisch seeks to express the intersect
 ion of life and music in her work. She has made multiple concerto appearan
 ces performing works by Chopin\, Rachmaninoff\, Mendelssohn\, and Saint-Sa
 ëns. She is passionate about investing in the local music community and a
 ctively collaborates with Chicago musicians on recital programs\, private 
 events\, and other professional endeavors.\n\nIn addition to her performan
 ce career\, she maintains a private teaching studio where she believes tec
 hnique and musicianship work together to foster a greater appreciation and
  love for the art of music. She was named the 2022 Top Teacher by Steinway
  & Sons in Chicago. She completed her MA in Piano at Eastern Illinois Univ
 ersity where she studied under Dr. Victor Cayres. Previous teachers includ
 e Thomas Pandolfi and Dr. Paul Kenyon.
LOCATION:St. Mark's Episcopal Church
URL:http://www.stmarksevanston.org
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
