BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Talks@EHC: Blanche Gildin & the Foundations of an Artistic Practic
 e
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T183000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T183000
UID:260203sHnR6i-xtkuscH3xHFjCfg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/qqb_9spmE0uk1inK1kVdRg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Blanche Gildin \\(1928-2024\\) was an Evanston-based artist wh
 ose studies at Chicago’s Institute of Design from 1947 to 1949 shaped he
 r artistic practice across more than seven decades. Like many women artist
 s of her generation\, she worked in private\, guided less by recognition t
 han by curiosity and discipline. Dr. Lara Allison from the School of the A
 rt Institute of Chicago and author of the just-published catalog Blanche G
 ildin: Back to the Bauhaus will discuss Gildin\, her work\, and the New Ba
 uhaus movement at the Institute of Design with the artist's daughter\, Bon
 ny Gildin and Jack Weiss of Design Evanston\, who also studied at the Inst
 itute of Design. Three of Gildin's works–recently accessioned into the E
 vanston History Center's permanent art collection–will be on view. FREE\
 , please RSVP
LOCATION:Evanston History Center
URL:https://evanstonhistorycenter.org/event/talksehc-blanche-gildin-the-ba
 uhaus-in-chicago-and-the-foundations-of-an-artistic-practice/
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
