BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Evanston Repair Café
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T100000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T120000
UID:250418C7pbPjx5MkGLggyZCAMr-A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/teDe3JnQGkm3V7zYBnDxeg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:"Never take broken for an answer" Following the Ifixit motto\,
  the Repair Café Volunteers will do their best to bring your beloved item
 s back to life... with your help!\n\nSo\, what is this all about?\n\nRepai
 r Café's are free meeting spaces where people fix things together. Beside
 s the obvious money saving\, RC's help keep stuff out of the landfill\, pr
 omote connection and collaboration\, skill-sharing and community self-reli
 ance.\n\nSo give it a try! Find that broken item you never brought yoursel
 f to throw away \\(remember\, there is no "away"!\\) and sign up for a slo
 t that matches the type or repair you need. Once at the Repair Café\, you
  will work together with our volunteers to repair your items.\n\nThese are
  our repair categories. Please sign up for ONE SINGLE SLOT per event. Addi
 tional slots will be deleted.\n\nSmall Appliances: Make sure you add make 
 and model when you sign up\, as well as a description of what is not worki
 ng.\n\nElectronics: Bring items fully charged and/or with ALL their power 
 cords. \\(Printers: bring the cable that connects it to your computer!\\) 
 Sorry\, no TV sets or VCRs!\n\nSewing: We focus on teaching you how to re
 pair\, so we do not provide alteration or tailoring services. Zippers: We 
 don't replace them but we can try to repair sliders.\n\nJewelry: Restringi
 ng\, fixing clasps or chains\, gluing\, basic cleaning and polishing We do
  not solder. Watch bands are not our specialty but we can try:\\)\n\nAt so
 me of our events\, you will find additional repair categories. Check the a
 ctual sign-up to see what is available.\n\nBikes: We provide basic repair
 s such as tightening loose bolts\, loosening stuck seats and stems\, chain
  cleaning and lubing\, shifting adjustments and brake alignment. \n\nPape
 r and Book Conservation: We will be able to provide you with guidelines an
 d advice on care and maintenance for your books\, paper art and photograph
 s\, as well as direct you to local conservation and heritage professionals
 .\n\nKnife Sharpening: Bring a knife or a pair of scissors to have them s
 harpened and to learn more about blade sharpening.\n\nSock darning and Bas
 ic Visible Mending: Bring your item and ideally\, the matching thread you
  want to use to learn how to darn your socks or mend your garment. Your it
 ems must be clean\, particularly clothing\, vacuum cleaner hoses\, filters
 \, air purifiers\, toasters\, blenders...\n\nItem Assembly/Small Furniture
  Repair: "Some assembly required" but you've lost the instructions? Bring
  it so we can work on it together. Small Furniture - Fixing\, gluing\, tig
 htening screws...\n\nPhone Help \\(No Hardware Repair\\): How do Google P
 hotos and ICloud work? How do you sync your Google Photos to your computer
 ? How do you enable accessibility functions?\n\nMusic Instruments: Musica
 l guidance\, instrumental consultations and suggestions. Care and repair r
 eferral suggestions for most instruments\, and music theory discussion and
  questions.\n\nSpare parts: Bring them if you know them!\n\nCo-sponsored w
 ith Climate Action Evanston. We are grateful to the Evanston Repair Café 
 volunteers for their expertise\, time\, and support.\n\nThe City of Evanst
 on is committed to promoting a Citywide culture of accessibility and inclu
 sivity. To request an accommodation for a program\, service\, or activity\
 , please call 847-866-2919 to make an ADA service request or fill out a r
 equest form online.
LOCATION:Robert Crown Branch Library
URL:https://evanstonlibrary.bibliocommons.com/events/67e6e1c4605e14c9dc5db
 cdd
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
