BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stefan Hillesheim: Album Release Party w. Special Guest
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T200000
UID:260311WWkv2seygEaF2AzdxeSdJw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/4r9bOGXhVk-JChjicTVCUA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Stefan Hillesheim is a German native who made the big move acr
 oss the Atlantic to chase his American Dream. In 2014\, Stefan first arriv
 ed in Los Angeles\, California\, to attend Musicians Institute \\(GIT\\)\,
  where he was awarded Most Improved Student. Soon after\, he began to play
  in renowned gospel churches and live music venues around the country. His
  signature finger-style guitar tone and driving rhythm guitar skills make 
 Stefan a high-demand session player. During his time in California\, Stefa
 n has performed and recorded with many notable artists\, including Bobby K
 imball \\(Toto\\)\, Ellis Hall \\(Tower of Power\\)\, Brent Carter \\(Aver
 age White Band\\)\, Emerson Cardenas \\(Santana\\)\, Frank Nitty \\(2Pac\\
 )\, and James Fortune. In 2022\, Stefan relocated to Chicago in pursuit of
  his love of the blues. Shortly after his arrival\, Stefan formed a band c
 omprised of seasoned Windy City musicians\, who perfectly complemented his
  style\, passion\, and love for the blues. The Chicago blues community wel
 comed Stefan with open arms - Stefan is best known for his slide guitar pl
 aying\, soulful vocals\, and dynamic live performances. Stefans main music
 al influences are Elmore James\, Albert King\, Jimi Hendrix\, Eric Clapton
 \, Derek Trucks\, and Otis Redding.
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/stefan-hillesheim-album-release-party-w-special-guest/17964556/
 2026-03-25T20
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
