BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jimmie Allen
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T193000
UID:260228yu6PPBaE70q7s2pMp7-CmA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/mww00_JhU0214iXGredLgA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Jimmie Allen is one of the most dynamic and boundary-pushing a
 rtists in music today. His journey from Milton\, Delaware to the pinnacle 
 of the music industry is powered by equal parts grit\, genre-bending ambit
 ion\, and an unmatched ability to connect with audiences worldwide. After 
 relocating to Nashville in 2007\, Allen spent years sharpening a sound tha
 t honors storytelling tradition while leaning into pop-forward energy that
  resonates across genres. That persistence paid off with his 2018 debut al
 bum Mercury Lane and the breakout single "Best Shot\," which became his fi
 rst Billboard Country Airplay No. 1. He followed with two more chart-toppe
 rs "Make Me Want To" and the stadium-ready "Freedom Was a Highway" with Br
 ad Paisley cementing his place among music's elite. Named ACM New Male Art
 ist and CMA New Artist of the Year in 2021\, and earning a Grammy nominati
 on for Best New Artist\, Allen has collaborated with legends including Nel
 ly\, Tim McGraw\, Jennifer Lopez\, and Dolly Parton.
LOCATION:Northlight Theatre
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/jimmie-allen/18248560/2026-04-17T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
