BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:O Jerusalem!  Crossroad of Three Faiths
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T213000
UID:2509105YiuK48kzU6OXdy2r70Q5A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/UtR9ljOKrk-MVZu4vas-vw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Ringing with urgency in our time\, this acclaimed program crea
 ted by Jeannette Sorrell returns in a fresh version. Honoring the peoples 
 whose music and faith brought such vibrancy to the Middle East\, 26 artist
 s from Jewish\, Palestinian\, Muslim\, and Christian backgrounds perform o
 n oud\, theorbo\, medieval harp\, zither\, strings\, and exotic percussion
 .\n\nIn this musical tour of the four quarters of Old Jerusalem \\(Jewish\
 , Christian\, Arab\, and Armenian\\)\, surprising cross-influences emerge.
  A Sephardic ballad leads to a classical Arabic love song\; selections fro
 m Monteverdi’s great Vespers of 1610 echo the exotic and rapturous sin
 ging of the Jewish cantors in the temples. The rhythms of daily life – l
 ove\, singing\, dancing and prayer – culminate in a joyous celebration o
 f shared humanity.
LOCATION:Nichols Concert Hall\, Music Institute of Chicago
URL:https://apollosfire.org/event/o-jerusalem-chicago/
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
