UID:260302E2hleMvxb0WalSELZGPL6A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/zzhmQigwzkCTM29VmN1cIw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Come to the Dawes House for coffee\, lunch\, and informal conv
 ersation around a variety of unique Evanston History topics. Feel free to 
 bring a brown bag lunch\; coffee and tea will be provided.\n\nUpcoming top
 ics:\n\nMarch 11: Evanston Women and the Fragile Nature of Legal Victories
  with Lori Osborne\, former director of the Evanston Women’s History Pr
 oject\n\nApril 8: Draining Evanston Part II: 21st Century with Dick Lanyo
 n\, former Executive Director of the Metropolitan Water Reclamation Distri
 ct of Greater Chicago\n\nMay 13: YMCA Camp Echo Through the Decades with 
 Katie Trippi\n\nJune 10: TBD!\n\nJuly 7: Disability Advocacy in Evanston 
 with Shore Services\n\nAugust 12: The History of Recreational Sailing on t
 he Great Lakes with Madeline Crispell\, Curator at the Chicago Maritime M
 useum
LOCATION:Evanston History Center
URL:https://evanstonhistorycenter.org/event/monthy-lunchtime-curiosity-caf
 e/2026-06-10/
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
